<paragraph id="8BD436C2870BAA1446A0F9ABDE50AD52" blockId="16.[189,1399,1625,1912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This species was described based on a single female specimen collected by the American limnologist and Amazon traveler Harriet Bell Merrill (
<date id="FFD51002870BAA1444C5F98CD83FACBC" box="[728,863,1662,1689]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1863" valueMax="1915">1863–1915</date>
) during a research trip to South America. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33870BAA144779F956D941AC9B" author="Rathbun" box="[356,545,1700,1726]" firstAuthor="Rathbun" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref21749" refString="Rathbun R. 1911. Report on the Progress and Condition of the U. S. National Museum for the Year ending June 30, 1910. Government Printing Office, Washington." type="book" year="1911">Rathbun (1911)</bibRefCitation>
, she sold to the 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07870BAA1444F6F956D825AC9B" box="[747,837,1700,1726]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
<specimenCount id="9D6DFD4B870BAA144552F951D89FAC9B" box="[847,1023,1699,1726]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="generic">500 specimens</specimenCount>
of insects collected during her expedition to 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652870BAA14477FF93BDACDACC6" box="[354,429,1737,1763]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, including probably the exemplar studied by Cockerell. The 
<typeStatus id="54D08860870BAA14429EF93BDF8AACC6" box="[1155,1258,1737,1763]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="13502A47870BAA1442E6F93BDE31ACC6" box="[1275,1361,1737,1763]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,763,789]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,720]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1398,265,720]" captionText="Fig. 11. Centris merrillae Cockerell, 1919, holotype, ♀ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534204). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722972" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722972/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) is housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07870BAA144729F91CDAEEAD2D" box="[308,398,1774,1800]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and has the following data label: Manaos 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652870BAA14459DF91CD8A8AD2D" box="[896,968,1774,1800]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
[printed]\ Miss HBMerrill Collector [printed] 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41870BAA144737F8E1D94EAD08" authority="Ckll" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1919" box="[298,558,1811,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merrillae">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0870BAA144737F8E1DA94AD08" box="[298,500,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Centris merrillae</emphasis>
Ckll
</taxonomicName>
Type. [handwritten]\ [red label] Type No. [printed] 21655 [handwritten] 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652870BAA1446A0F8CADB8FAD77" box="[189,239,1848,1874]" name="United States of America" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">U.S.</collectingCountry>
N.M. [printed]\ [yellow label] USNM ENT 00534204 [barcode] [printed]\\ DO NOT REMOVE SI DB Reference Not a property tag T. Schultz 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07870BAA1444DBF8ACD840AD5D" box="[710,800,1886,1912]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
[printed]. The 
<typeStatus id="54D08860870BAA1445CCF8AFDF58AD52" box="[977,1080,1885,1911]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
is in good condition.
</paragraph>
